Description: A limestone slab with the remains of a Latin inscription of ten lines. A dedication, by the emperors Diocletian and Maximian, of the camp of the first ala of the Thracian cavalry, to Jupiter Hercules and Victory.
Excavator/field collector: Excavated by: Prof Francis Llewellyn Griffith
Bibliographic references: CIL III / Inscriptiones Asiae, provinciarum Europae Graecarum, Illyrici Latinae (13578)
